{"slug": "api/oauth/google", "modified": "2014-10-16T08:16:09", "site": {"template": "doc.html", "url": "http://quantmind.github.io/lux", "date": "2014-10-16T10-28-06", "media": "/media", "name": "Lux", "lux_version": "0.1.1-alpha.1", "template_engine": null, "python_version": "3.4.1", "year": 2014}, "api_url": "http://quantmind.github.io/lux/jsonapi/docs/api/oauth/google", "head": {}, "name": "api_oauth_google", "html": {"main": "<section id=\"page-header\" class=\"page-header-outer api_oauth_google-header\">\n    <div class=\"layer\">\n        <div class=\"page-header\">\n            <div class=\"container fullpage\">\n                <div class=\"row fullpage\">\n                    <div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\n                        <breadcrumbs></breadcrumbs>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<div id=\"page-main\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"api_oauth_google-main col-md-12\">\n                <div class=\"center-block\" style=\"max-width: 900px\" data-highlight data-hash-scroll>\n                    <div class=\"section\" id=\"module-lux.extensions.oauth.google\">\n<span id=\"google-integration\"></span><span id=\"extension-google\"></span><h1>Google Integration<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#module-lux.extensions.oauth.google\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p>This module integrates Google <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://developers.google.com/accounts/docs/OAuth2\">OAuth2</a> services and APIs with lux.</p>\n<p>When the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">google</span></tt> dictionary is included into the <a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../params#std:setting-OAUTH_PROVIDERS\"><tt class=\"xref std std-setting docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">OAUTH_PROVIDERS</span></tt></a>\ndictionary, the <em class=\"xref std std-ref\">google angular module</em> is added to the\n<em class=\"xref std std-ref\">javascript context object</em> which can be used by AngularJS if the\n<a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../angular#module-lux.extensions.angular\" title=\"lux.extensions.angular\"><tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.angular</span></tt></a> module is included in the list of\n<a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../params#std:setting-EXTENSIONS\"><tt class=\"xref std std-setting docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">EXTENSIONS</span></tt></a> of your application.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"google-analytics\">\n<h2>Google analytics<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#google-analytics\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>To use google analytics add the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">analytics</span></tt> dictionary to the\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">google</span></tt> dictionary in <a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../params#std:setting-OAUTH_PROVIDERS\"><tt class=\"xref std std-setting docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">OAUTH_PROVIDERS</span></tt></a>:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre>OAUTH_PROVIDERS = {\n    ...,\n    &#39;google&#39;: {\n        ...,\n        &#39;analytics&#39;: {\n            &#39;id&#39;: &#39;UA-54439804-2&#39;,\n            ...\n        }\n    }\n}\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n<p>When using google analytics integration with <a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../angular#module-lux.extensions.angular\" title=\"lux.extensions.angular\"><tt class=\"xref py py-mod docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">lux.extensions.angular</span></tt></a>\nin <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"http://angular-ui.github.io/ui-router/site\">ui.router</a> mode (<a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"../params#std:setting-ANGULAR_UI_ROUTER\"><tt class=\"xref std std-setting docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">ANGULAR_UI_ROUTER</span></tt></a> set to <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">True</span></tt>) one\nmust be aware that <strong>pageview</strong> events are not triggered anymore.</p>\n<p>To handle this situation the <em class=\"xref std std-ref\">google angular module</em>\ninteracts with google analytics to register pageviews and custom events\nby listening for the <cite>$stateChangeSuccess</cite> event.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"google-maps\">\n<h2>Google maps<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#google-maps\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>To use google map, a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">simple_key</span></tt> entry in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">google</span></tt> config dictionary must\nbe specified. The simple key is used by google to identify your project when\nyou do not need to access user data:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre>OAUTH_PROVIDERS = {\n    ...,\n    &#39;google&#39;: {\n        &#39;simple_key&#39;: &#39;...&#39;\n        &#39;map_sensor&#39;: True,\n        ...\n    }\n}\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<div class='small hidden-print text-muted' id='page-footer'>\n    <div class='container'>\n        <div class='row'>\n            <div class='block col-sm-5'>\n                <div class='hidden-xs'>\n                    <ul class=\"fa-ul text-left\">\n    <li><i class=\"fa-li fa fa-copyright\"></i>2014 <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></li>\n    <li>Site build with Lux on python 3.4.1</li>\n    <li>Docs build with <a href=\"http://sphinx-doc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sphinx</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/changelog\">Changelog</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/api/\">API</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/EXTENSIONS/\">Extensions</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/images\">Images</a></li>\n</ul>\n                </div>\n                <div class='text-center visible-xs'>\n                    <ul class=\"fa-ul text-left\">\n    <li><i class=\"fa-li fa fa-copyright\"></i>2014 <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></li>\n    <li>Site build with Lux on python 3.4.1</li>\n    <li>Docs build with <a href=\"http://sphinx-doc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sphinx</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/changelog\">Changelog</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/api/\">API</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/docs/EXTENSIONS/\">Extensions</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"http://quantmind.github.io/lux/images\">Images</a></li>\n</ul>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class='block col-sm-2 text-center'>\n                <div class='hidden-xs'>\n                    <p><a href='#top' title=\"Lux\" class=\"hover-opacity\">\n    <img height=50 title='Lux' src='http://quantmind.github.io/lux/media/luxsite/lux.png' alt='Lux'>\n</a></p>\n                </div>\n                <div class='visible-xs'>\n                    <p><a href='https://twitter.com/quantmind' title='Follow quantmind on twitter'>\n<i class='fa fa-twitter fa-2x'></i></a>\n<a href='https://plus.google.com/+QuantmindPlus' title='Follow quantmind on google+'>\n<i class='fa fa-google-plus-square fa-2x'></i></a>\n<a href='https://www.facebook.com/quantmind' title='Follow quantmind on facebook'>\n<i class='fa fa-facebook-square fa-2x'></i></a>\n<a href='https://github.com/quantmind/lux' title='Lux on github'>\n<i class='fa fa-github fa-2x'></i></a></p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class='block col-sm-5'>\n                <div class='text-right hidden-xs'>\n                    <p><a href='https://twitter.com/quantmind' title='Follow quantmind on twitter'>\n<i class='fa fa-twitter fa-2x'></i></a>\n<a href='https://plus.google.com/+QuantmindP